    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "in (1), `T` is a very general notion of \"transaction\" (as in CS literature, not as in Ethereum specifically) with `t` being temporal steps of such \"transactions\".\r\n\r\nin (2-4), (1) is reformulated into something much better approximating what the Ethereum system is with the notional blocks and transactions.\r\n\r\nas such (2-4) is not strictly derivable from (1), but rather a conceptual specialisation of (1) - this is very much on purpose. much of the value of these equations comes from their simplicity: this is the preamble and it's important to be able to describe concepts generally and concisely.\r\n\r\n",
